HEADWORD: di-iodotyrosine
<hw>di-iodotyrosine</hw></mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem., Med.)</fld> <def>a chemical substance
consisting of tyrosine with two hydrogen atoms on the benzene ring
replaced by iodine atoms.</def> <note>The isomer
<chname>3,5-diiodotyrosine</chname> is an inhibitor of thyroid
function.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

